<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>org-mode will use an ellipsis (org-ellipsis) at the end of folded headings to represent its hidden contents. You can edit org-ellipsis to display a different string of characters, but is there a way to represent folded headings in the fringe?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/DANGUS_77"> /u/DANGUS_77 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wfp8fr/representing_orgmode_folding_in_the_fringe/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wfp8fr/representing_orgmode_folding_in_the_fringe/">[comments]</a></span>